      "Tall trees line both sides of a wide and rocky path, a mixture of grey-barked haon mingling with shingle monirs, quaking aspens, and silvery beeches to create a thick canopy overhead.  Dappled sunlight streams down to the forest floor in thin beams, encouraging the growth of wild flowers, like delicate white may apples and lavender lady slippers.  The switchback lead up toward a mountain forest and down toward a canyon."
